reply_text:
@HCHecxz

Do you have the same problem when TV shows pull back the curtain and show and discuss  the creative making the show? Documentaries about the making of certain tv shows and movies have been out there for decades. No one complains about that.

The Walking Dead literally showed behind the scenes stuff on the episode where two major characters were killed. Granted, they didn’t do that on the actual show. They talked about the creative process after and the make up used to make the scene look good.

@blackstewiegriffin The kids who saw WrestleMania already knows about this show. They had Cole break the fourth wall on Mania and announce that the show would delve into the creative process and how storylines are created. 

They literally broke the 4th wall just to promote this show. You do that during a commercial. Not on the actual show

And most kids knows it’s not real anyway. They just appreciate it like any other TV show with fight choreography.
